WEBVTT

00:01:42.160 --> 00:01:44.039
I want to drive trucks because

00:01:44.240 --> 00:01:45.000
Every time I set out,

00:01:45.000 --> 00:01:46.039
I get to go somewhere different

00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:46.960
And see different scenery.

00:01:48.080 --> 00:01:48.840
But I think

00:01:49.120 --> 00:01:50.240
From what your parents want,

00:01:50.520 --> 00:01:51.840
A boat captain or the mahjong parlor,

00:01:52.039 --> 00:01:53.200
You have to inherit one of them.

00:01:53.560 --> 00:01:55.520
That's the fallback they left me.

00:01:56.039 --> 00:01:56.880
Actually,

00:01:57.280 --> 00:01:58.640
Fishermen all hope their children

00:01:58.640 --> 00:01:59.400
Can come back to shore.

00:01:59.520 --> 00:02:00.400
Take my dad, for example.

00:02:00.720 --> 00:02:01.680
My dad is like a shark.

00:02:01.880 --> 00:02:03.000
He loves thrashing around in the sea.

00:02:03.600 --> 00:02:04.720
I'm a wild dog.

00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:05.320
So I have to...

00:02:05.320 --> 00:02:06.880
I have to run wild on the road.

00:02:08.960 --> 00:02:10.120
Is that a dog bark?

00:02:10.400 --> 00:02:11.120
That's a wolf.

00:02:11.160 --> 00:02:12.040
I... I'm a wild wolf.

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:12.760
I'm a wild wolf. A wild wolf.

00:02:12.760 --> 00:02:13.240
Who

00:02:13.240 --> 00:02:14.840
Calls himself a wild dog?

00:02:14.880 --> 00:02:15.600
Slip of the tongue.

00:02:16.520 --> 00:02:16.960
Qing Ye.

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:18.120
What do you want to do in the future?

00:02:21.600 --> 00:02:22.280
I want to make money.

00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:24.120
Pretty direct.

00:02:24.440 --> 00:02:25.040
Just money?

00:02:25.200 --> 00:02:25.760
Nothing else? Yes.

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:27.720
That's pretty shallow.

00:02:28.640 --> 00:02:29.560
It's practical.

00:02:29.760 --> 00:02:30.440
Once I make money,

00:02:30.680 --> 00:02:31.280
I can do

00:02:31.280 --> 00:02:32.680
What I want to do.

00:02:33.079 --> 00:02:34.400
Money gives me security.

00:02:34.720 --> 00:02:35.920
And I can protect my family

00:02:35.920 --> 00:02:36.560
From storms.

00:02:38.079 --> 00:02:38.520
What about you?

00:02:39.079 --> 00:02:39.920
Do you have any goals?

00:02:40.320 --> 00:02:40.760
Me?

00:02:41.800 --> 00:02:42.200
No.

00:02:43.640 --> 00:02:44.600
No dreams?

00:02:45.560 --> 00:02:47.200
I used to want to be a pilot.

00:02:47.760 --> 00:02:48.360
And now?

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:49.640
Not anymore.

00:02:50.360 --> 00:02:51.120
People without dreams

00:02:51.120 --> 00:02:52.240
Can still live good lives.

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:56.040
Don't keep grilling Wu.

00:02:56.320 --> 00:02:56.960
Compared to Wu,

00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:57.880
We want to know more about you.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:02:59.680
What about me?

00:03:01.120 --> 00:03:01.960
For example,

00:03:02.680 --> 00:03:03.080
Girls like you

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:04.160
From the city.

00:03:04.640 --> 00:03:05.640
What kind of boys do you like?

00:03:07.960 --> 00:03:08.880
What are you doing?

00:03:08.920 --> 00:03:09.640
I mean,

00:03:10.200 --> 00:03:12.280
By "like,"

00:03:13.080 --> 00:03:14.680
I mean admire,

00:03:14.760 --> 00:03:16.079
Respect, look up to.

00:03:16.120 --> 00:03:17.240
You're reading too much into it.

00:03:18.520 --> 00:03:19.200
Well,

00:03:19.880 --> 00:03:21.400
I like

00:03:22.520 --> 00:03:23.320
Boys with good grades.

00:03:24.840 --> 00:03:26.280
Then I'm out, huh?

00:03:26.520 --> 00:03:28.400
Go look at yourself by the sea.

00:03:28.520 --> 00:03:29.640
Wash your face and come back.

00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:31.640
If I start working hard now,

00:03:31.640 --> 00:03:32.480
Is there still time?

00:03:32.600 --> 00:03:33.560
Why ask me?

00:03:33.760 --> 00:03:34.840
You took two years off school.

00:03:34.840 --> 00:03:36.040
We're about the same level.

00:03:36.440 --> 00:03:37.360
Then it's too late.

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:39.520
Of course it's not too late.

00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:41.360
When it comes to studying,

00:03:41.800 --> 00:03:42.760
As long as you want to start,

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:44.800
It's never too late.

00:03:49.240 --> 00:03:50.320
Then let's work hard and try.

00:03:51.680 --> 00:03:52.040
Come on.

00:03:52.079 --> 00:03:52.840
Come on. Another toast.

00:03:53.400 --> 00:03:54.079
Good luck to you.

00:03:54.120 --> 00:03:54.880
Kyle! Kyle Hao!

00:03:54.960 --> 00:03:55.200
Come on.

00:03:55.440 --> 00:03:58.160
You really will succeed.

00:06:03.880 --> 00:06:04.760
You're up so early.

00:06:07.080 --> 00:06:07.880
I couldn't sleep.

00:06:08.800 --> 00:06:09.240
What about you?

00:06:10.080 --> 00:06:11.280
Up this early to watch the sea?

00:06:12.680 --> 00:06:13.520
I couldn't sleep either.

00:06:14.640 --> 00:06:16.000
I came out for a walk

00:06:16.640 --> 00:06:17.600
And to think about some things.

00:06:19.040 --> 00:06:19.520
What things?

00:06:21.000 --> 00:06:21.800
Yesterday you asked me

00:06:22.280 --> 00:06:23.120
If I had a dream.

00:06:24.040 --> 00:06:24.720
I said no.

00:06:25.840 --> 00:06:26.680
Actually, it's not that I don't.

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:29.680
I just haven't figured it out yet.

00:06:32.680 --> 00:06:34.280
If you haven't, take your time.

00:06:34.840 --> 00:06:35.800
Like you said,

00:06:36.200 --> 00:06:37.680
Some people don't have dreams

00:06:38.240 --> 00:06:39.280
And still live well, don't they?

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:42.640
But there's one thing

00:06:43.400 --> 00:06:44.240
I've figured out.

00:06:44.880 --> 00:06:45.360
What?

00:06:47.159 --> 00:06:47.920
I want to go to college.

00:06:53.760 --> 00:06:54.680
College?

00:06:55.120 --> 00:06:55.840
That's it?

00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:00.320
College

00:07:01.360 --> 00:07:02.120
Can't be a bad choice.

00:07:06.680 --> 00:07:07.560
Why

00:07:08.680 --> 00:07:10.320
Did you suddenly make up your mind?

00:07:13.160 --> 00:07:13.840
Because

00:07:23.080 --> 00:07:24.240
I want to try

00:07:24.840 --> 00:07:25.920
What it feels like to be a good student.

00:08:07.680 --> 00:08:09.520
See? I told you.

00:08:09.760 --> 00:08:12.400
What parent wouldn't agree

00:08:12.400 --> 00:08:13.600
When a kid wants to go back to school?

00:08:13.960 --> 00:08:15.440
Besides, I saw her dad's

00:08:15.440 --> 00:08:16.440
Condition too.

00:08:16.600 --> 00:08:17.440
He isn't someone

00:08:17.440 --> 00:08:18.880
Who can't be reasoned with.

00:08:19.760 --> 00:08:20.200
Exactly.

00:08:20.240 --> 00:08:21.160
Just as I expected.

00:08:21.520 --> 00:08:22.920
Unlike our Wu.

00:08:23.360 --> 00:08:24.640
To get him back to school,

00:08:24.640 --> 00:08:25.680
You have to beg him.

00:08:26.000 --> 00:08:26.720
Good thing

00:08:27.080 --> 00:08:28.600
Qing Ye stepped in herself.

00:08:28.840 --> 00:08:29.320
Grandma.

00:08:29.720 --> 00:08:31.600
Your favorite sea urchin egg custard.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:32.320
You eat first. Okay.

00:08:32.400 --> 00:08:32.840
See?

00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:35.000
My grandson is still the most filial.

00:08:36.600 --> 00:08:37.679
Here, Mom. Have some soup.

00:08:37.720 --> 00:08:38.880
Okay. Thank you. Thank you.

00:08:39.159 --> 00:08:39.600
Ye.

00:08:39.840 --> 00:08:41.679
I heard you're forming

00:08:42.120 --> 00:08:43.000
With Shi Min

00:08:43.240 --> 00:08:44.920
Some kind of study group

00:08:44.920 --> 00:08:46.280
Or study squad?

00:08:46.520 --> 00:08:47.920
Just a study group.

00:08:48.880 --> 00:08:50.320
Since everyone needs to study,

00:08:50.520 --> 00:08:51.280
We might as well get together

00:08:51.400 --> 00:08:52.520
And help each other.

00:08:54.080 --> 00:08:55.760
Then what about Wu?

00:08:55.960 --> 00:08:57.400
I'll join when I have time.

00:08:57.880 --> 00:08:58.880
He's so good already.

00:08:58.880 --> 00:09:00.600
At his level, he can study on his own.

00:09:00.680 --> 00:09:01.520
No way.

00:09:01.800 --> 00:09:02.880
I've been out of school so long.

00:09:03.120 --> 00:09:04.000
If I have questions,

00:09:04.280 --> 00:09:05.320
I still need to ask

00:09:05.440 --> 00:09:06.960
Zhazhating's outstanding educator,

00:09:07.280 --> 00:09:07.960
Teacher Qing Ye.

00:09:10.560 --> 00:09:11.680
Wu, since when

00:09:11.720 --> 00:09:13.200
Did you get so good with words?

00:09:13.280 --> 00:09:14.880
I've learned by watching Teacher Qing Ye.

00:09:15.080 --> 00:09:15.840
Here, have some egg.

00:09:17.440 --> 00:09:19.360
Study hard, ask questions, keep at it.

00:09:19.520 --> 00:09:20.360
From now on,

00:09:20.360 --> 00:09:22.960
Study hard with Teacher Qing Ye.

00:09:23.800 --> 00:09:24.320
Teacher Qing Ye.

00:09:24.320 --> 00:09:25.240
You're too kind. Too kind.

00:09:25.240 --> 00:09:25.880
Come on. Try this.

00:09:25.920 --> 00:09:26.800
Auntie's scrambled eggs.

00:09:26.800 --> 00:09:27.520
Thank you.

00:09:27.560 --> 00:09:29.160
Teacher Qing Ye.

00:09:30.200 --> 00:09:31.240
Teacher Qing Ye, have some fish.

00:09:31.680 --> 00:09:32.520
It's good. It's good.

00:09:32.560 --> 00:09:33.800
Watch out for bones.

00:09:36.680 --> 00:09:37.520
Leave it. I'll do it.

00:09:38.920 --> 00:09:39.920
What's hard about washing dishes?

00:09:40.160 --> 00:09:41.200
I've even shucked oysters.

00:09:42.520 --> 00:09:43.760
Aren't you supposed to tutor me?

00:09:44.160 --> 00:09:45.080
You need to prepare, right?

00:09:47.240 --> 00:09:47.800
All right.

00:09:48.120 --> 00:09:49.880
I'll go prepare the questions.

00:09:49.960 --> 00:09:50.760
I'll wait upstairs.

00:09:50.960 --> 00:09:51.880
Okay. Ten minutes.

00:09:53.960 --> 00:09:54.520
Wait.

00:09:55.840 --> 00:09:56.600
Give me the apron.

00:09:58.720 --> 00:09:59.240
Right, right.

00:10:45.360 --> 00:10:46.600
Sis, what are you washing?

00:10:47.000 --> 00:10:47.720
Clothes.

00:10:48.840 --> 00:10:49.920
You come here to do laundry too?

00:10:50.600 --> 00:10:51.680
Yes. I'm collecting towels.

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:55.200
More cardboard boxes piled up.

00:10:55.520 --> 00:10:56.840
Those are Zhang's, right?

00:10:58.120 --> 00:10:58.720
Probably.

00:11:00.920 --> 00:11:01.520
Zhang.

00:11:03.000 --> 00:11:03.720
Zhang.

00:11:05.200 --> 00:11:06.720
What decade is this?

00:11:06.960 --> 00:11:08.480
Why keep so many cardboard boxes?

00:11:08.520 --> 00:11:09.600
Get rid of them.

00:11:10.640 --> 00:11:12.520
They won't sell for much anyway.

00:11:12.880 --> 00:11:14.080
If you run into

00:11:14.120 --> 00:11:15.120
A cigarette butt

00:11:15.120 --> 00:11:15.760
Or something,

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:17.000
And it starts a fire,

00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:17.920
What then?

00:11:18.800 --> 00:11:19.640
Zhang.

00:11:20.040 --> 00:11:20.760
Okay, okay.

00:11:20.880 --> 00:11:21.800
I know, Lanfang.

00:11:22.000 --> 00:11:22.880
Hurry up.

00:11:33.760 --> 00:11:34.840
What happened to ten minutes?

00:11:35.600 --> 00:11:36.240
Washing dishes

00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:37.600
And taking off the apron took ten minutes.

00:11:40.320 --> 00:11:41.760
I tied it into a knot by accident.

00:11:42.520 --> 00:11:42.960
Come on.

00:11:43.560 --> 00:11:44.200
Do the problems.

00:11:45.400 --> 00:11:46.040
Let's treat it as a placement test.

00:11:46.200 --> 00:11:46.760
After this,

00:11:46.960 --> 00:11:48.080
We'll practice based on your weak spots.

00:11:49.240 --> 00:11:49.880
Just start.

00:11:51.680 --> 00:11:52.120
Take your time.

00:11:52.960 --> 00:11:53.600
I'll stay with you.

00:11:55.320 --> 00:11:55.680
Okay.

00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:23.440
ABCD.

00:12:23.440 --> 00:12:26.040
The base ABCD is a rhombus.

00:12:26.840 --> 00:12:28.760
This side is length four.

00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:30.960
And this side is length two.

00:12:31.600 --> 00:12:33.040
What you need to prove

00:12:33.200 --> 00:12:34.440
Is that this line

00:12:34.800 --> 00:12:36.080
And this inclined plane

00:12:36.520 --> 00:12:37.720
Are parallel.

00:12:38.080 --> 00:12:38.880
How do we prove that?

00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:40.600
First, draw an auxiliary line.

00:12:40.720 --> 00:12:42.200
Once you prove these two angles

00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:43.600
Are both ninety degrees,

00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:45.360
You prove it's parallel

00:12:45.560 --> 00:12:46.520
To this plane.

00:12:46.560 --> 00:12:47.040
Right?

00:12:50.320 --> 00:12:50.640
Right.

00:12:50.640 --> 00:12:52.320
Don't look at me. Did you get it?

00:12:52.520 --> 00:12:53.040
I got it.

00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:53.960
Good. You got it.

00:12:54.000 --> 00:12:54.880
Apply it to another one. Here.

00:12:55.400 --> 00:12:56.760
This is similar. Geometry too.

00:12:56.760 --> 00:12:58.040
Try this one for me.

00:12:58.960 --> 00:13:00.160
AA1 equals four.

00:13:00.400 --> 00:13:01.320
AB2 equals two.

00:13:02.680 --> 00:13:04.720
MN is parallel to the plane.

00:13:05.320 --> 00:13:07.360
Prove this is parallel to this.

00:13:07.920 --> 00:13:08.920
It's not on this plane.

00:13:39.880 --> 00:13:41.200
Youth is wonderful.

00:13:41.320 --> 00:13:42.720
Learning never ends.

00:13:43.720 --> 00:13:43.960
Here.

00:13:43.960 --> 00:13:45.400
They're still studying?

00:13:45.400 --> 00:13:46.400
Yes.

00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:49.680
Study by lamplight through the night,

00:13:50.000 --> 00:13:52.400
That's exactly when young men should read.

00:13:53.120 --> 00:13:54.040
Can I have some water?

00:13:54.240 --> 00:13:55.280
Yes, yes, yes.

00:13:56.000 --> 00:13:57.080
Wu is still young.

00:13:57.840 --> 00:13:59.960
He has a long road ahead.

00:14:00.520 --> 00:14:01.880
He needs to study more

00:14:02.120 --> 00:14:03.760
To have a better future.

00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:05.920
Yes, yes. Exactly.

00:14:06.080 --> 00:14:07.520
We can't always let Wu

00:14:07.560 --> 00:14:08.800
Worry about this family.

00:14:09.640 --> 00:14:11.240
Seeing the kids work so hard,

00:14:11.320 --> 00:14:12.320
I need to try harder too.

00:14:14.280 --> 00:14:14.960
I know.

00:14:14.960 --> 00:14:17.560
Xuan Island has been doing well lately.

00:14:18.400 --> 00:14:19.720
As the boss lady,

00:14:20.040 --> 00:14:20.800
You're very successful.

00:14:23.000 --> 00:14:23.880
Mom, do you know?

00:14:24.360 --> 00:14:26.760
Since Xuan Island reopened,

00:14:26.840 --> 00:14:28.320
We have way more customers than before.

00:14:28.720 --> 00:14:30.320
Now everyone knows

00:14:30.680 --> 00:14:31.760
That I, Li Lanfang,

00:14:31.800 --> 00:14:33.280
Have all five certificates,

00:14:33.360 --> 00:14:34.880
So they feel safer.

00:14:36.280 --> 00:14:37.000
So to speak,

00:14:37.520 --> 00:14:39.320
Even a setback can have a silver lining.

00:14:39.600 --> 00:14:40.400
Sometimes bad things

00:14:40.440 --> 00:14:41.640
Can turn into good things.

00:14:42.520 --> 00:14:43.040
Exactly.

00:14:43.400 --> 00:14:44.240
I want

00:14:44.800 --> 00:14:46.320
To ride this momentum

00:14:46.880 --> 00:14:48.560
And expand my hairdressing career.

00:14:51.520 --> 00:14:52.320
Tell me about it.

00:14:54.240 --> 00:14:56.000
Recently, I saw online

00:14:56.760 --> 00:14:58.520
That the hottest thing now

00:14:58.560 --> 00:14:59.720
Is updos.

00:15:00.320 --> 00:15:01.240
I'm planning

00:15:01.480 --> 00:15:02.720
To go learn it.

00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:16.000
What do you think?

00:15:16.360 --> 00:15:16.760
Some parts

00:15:20.960 --> 00:15:21.920
Of your writing

00:15:22.640 --> 00:15:23.320
Are hard to follow.

00:15:23.920 --> 00:15:25.000
Which ones? Let me see.

00:15:33.560 --> 00:15:35.160
Your essay is

00:15:35.520 --> 00:15:36.560
A little weak.

00:15:37.880 --> 00:15:39.120
After all these years,

00:15:39.560 --> 00:15:40.960
I've forgotten almost all the words.

00:15:41.440 --> 00:15:42.000
My English

00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:42.960
Wasn't very good before anyway.

00:15:44.080 --> 00:15:45.200
Memorizing words is too hard.

00:15:45.840 --> 00:15:46.520
They know me,

00:15:46.680 --> 00:15:47.360
But I don't know them.

00:15:50.560 --> 00:15:51.520
Do you know the Ebbinghaus

00:15:51.520 --> 00:15:52.400
Forgetting curve?

00:15:54.160 --> 00:15:54.600
What?

00:15:54.920 --> 00:15:56.680
The Ebbinghaus forgetting curve.

00:15:58.440 --> 00:16:00.320
I think I've heard of it.

00:16:00.800 --> 00:16:01.520
It works like this.

00:16:02.400 --> 00:16:03.400
The Y-axis here

00:16:03.400 --> 00:16:04.840
Is the amount remembered.

00:16:05.200 --> 00:16:07.160
The X-axis here

00:16:07.400 --> 00:16:08.840
Is the number of days

00:16:08.840 --> 00:16:09.760
After you learn something.

00:16:10.720 --> 00:16:12.520
As time passes,

00:16:12.840 --> 00:16:14.520
What you remember

00:16:14.680 --> 00:16:16.000
Gradually gets forgotten.

00:16:17.400 --> 00:16:18.000
No wonder.

00:16:18.400 --> 00:16:19.560
I was wondering why I forgot everything.

00:16:20.360 --> 00:16:21.120
So,

00:16:21.720 --> 00:16:23.200
You need to keep memorizing,

00:16:23.560 --> 00:16:24.760
Reviewing,

00:16:24.760 --> 00:16:26.160
And reinforcing.

00:16:26.400 --> 00:16:27.880
Of course, don't make it painful.

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:28.520
For example,

00:16:29.000 --> 00:16:30.000
Watching TV shows

00:16:30.200 --> 00:16:31.280
Or listening to music

00:16:32.040 --> 00:16:34.200
Can all be ways to fragmented learning.

00:16:36.240 --> 00:16:37.520
So you have to push me more.

00:16:37.560 --> 00:16:39.200
Make me do more papers and problems.

00:16:41.840 --> 00:16:42.760
As long as I keep memorizing,

00:16:43.560 --> 00:16:43.920
Once memorize it,

00:16:44.640 --> 00:16:45.400
I'll use it someday.

00:16:45.920 --> 00:16:46.680
